  <prompt>
    Cross-pillar Phase C integration test exercising all six exit criteria + Q7
    expansion criterion in a single end-to-end flow. Test scenarios:
    1. **Workspace state in prompt**: open 3 tabs (2 visible, 1 not); ask "what's on the
       workspace?"; verify agent answers correctly referencing only visible tabs.
    2. **Trace widget event ordering**: invoke `/summarize` flow; verify Context pane
       trace widget shows ordered timeline of tool calls + knowledge retrievals + node
       executions + decisions.
    3. **Memory composition**: prior-session matter analysis is retrievable in current
       session via embedding similarity (task 066).
    4. **Conflict resolution**: simulate user edit → agent update attempt with stale
       expected timestamp → verify handler refuses + agent re-reads + re-attempts.
    5. **Pinned memory persistence**: "remember X" via chat → reload session → verify X
       appears in pinned memory list widget (task 070) + agent prompt composition (task
       067).
    6. **Q7 UI**: create pinned item via UI (task 070); verify it appears in chat memory
       composition; delete via UI; verify removal.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior QA engineer / integration test author with familiarity across Phase C
    deliverables.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All 6 scenarios pass end-to-end. Failures pinpoint specific Phase C task for
    remediation before exit gate (079).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
